this is the opposite of the process described in textbooks and built into economic models , which always assume that financial expectations adapt to reality , not the other way round .
in a classic example of reflexivity , when China &apos;s stock @-@ market boom turned into July &apos;s bust , the government responded with a $ 200 billion attempt to support prices , closely followed by a small devaluation of the previously stable renminbi .
