that scenario now looks all the more likely .
why , then , did the European Commission remain silent ?
the answer appears to be that it feared negative reactions from the three governments involved in the merger talks , and believed that its own authority would suffer from any public rebuff .
the persistent rumor circulating among defense company executives is that soon after news of the proposed merger leaked , the weekly commissioners &quot; meeting chaired by Commission President José Manuel Barroso was enjoined to keep silent on the matter in order to avoid any potential dangers .
